div.p: All user have a Primary Account (Wallet Address). User can enable/disable any feature at any time. Enabling for the first time creates a Protocol Wallet Address that is associated with the Primary Account. Only the user knows this address is theirs thus providing anonymity. User can set preferences for the amount of exposure/privacy for each Protocol Address individually.
